                    "description": "Stewart Blusson Postdoctoral Research Fellow in condensed matter and quantum information theory.\n\nResearch focus:\nquantum condensed matter, semiconductor-superconductor hybrid structures, topological superconductors, strongly interacting quantum matter and quantum chaos, quantum error correction with augmented topological stabilizer codes.\n\nAnalytical methods:\ngeneral condensed matter and quantum information theory, Greens functions, Schwinger-Dyson equations (equilibrium and non-equilibrium), quantum field theory, Hamiltonian toy models, topological qubits, quantum error-correction with stabilizer codes, open quantum systems, Lindblad equations, kinetic Monte-Carlo.\n\nNumerical methods:\nsuperconductor-semiconductor hybrid structures as lattice models in Python Numpy-Scipy via the Kwant and Pybinding packages, Schwinger-Dyson and Bethe-Salpeter equations with Python Numpy-Scipy and FFT algorithms, open quantum systems simulation using Python Numpy-Scipy with QuTiP and kinetic Monte-Carlo equations, quantum error-correction via Kolmogorov's Blossom algorithm; simulations were carried out on local machines and on Linux-based HPC clusters at SBQMI, UBC Vancouver, and in the Compute Canada network.",
